title.narrative: By end of 2019, communities in Mali have new goods and services for a sustainable access to safe drinking water and basic sanitation, especially in rural areas and areas affected by humanitarian situations.

description.narrative: UNICEF fostered an improved enabling environment for rural sanitation and water services in Mali by strengthening Community-led Total Sanitation (CLTS), developing WASH marketing approach and tools, and strengthening national planning and monitoring capacities. UNICEF contributed to address water access and needs in emergency and build population resilience in regions affected by the crisis. With UNICEF direct support in 2019, 74,674 people (37,955 children) gained access to improved water sources, 48,361 people (24,660 children) are living in 55 newly ODF certified communities and over 133,000 people (67,830 children) in humanitarian situations have been provided safe water through short-term water emergency response. | Status:Met | As-of Date:06/02/2020
